1. CORE ARCHITECTURE CHANGES (The "Gateway" Pattern)
-------------------------------------------------------------------
We moved away from a generic "one-size-fits-all" login to a strictly defined
Role-Based Access Control (RBAC) system.

OLD WAY:
- Users login with Email/Phone + Password/OTP mixed together.
- Backend guesses who they are (inefficient and error-prone).
- Frontend used generic API calls like `passwordLoginApi`.

NEW WAY:
- STEP 1: "Gatekeeper" (Detect User)
  - Input is analyzed first.
  - Email -> Admin
  - "STF..." ID -> Agent
  - Mobile Number -> Customer
- STEP 2: Specific Login Routes
  - Admin -> /api/auth/admin/login (Password)
  - Agent -> /api/auth/agent/login (Password)
  - Customer -> /api/auth/login/otp (Mobile + OTP)

